Responsible Office Office of the Chief Financial Officer 1 POLICY It is the National Aeronautics and Space Administration s NASA policy to comply with the Chief Financial Officers Act of 1990 which states that the Agency Chief Financial Officer CFO directs manages and provides policy guidance and oversight of Agency financial management personnel activities and operations 2 APPLICABILITY a This NASA Policy Directive NPD is applicable to NASA Headquarters and NASA Centers including Component Facilities and Technical and Service Support Centers This language applies to the Jet Propulsion Laboratory a Federally Funded Research and Development Center other contractors grant recipients or parties to agreements only to the extent specified or referenced in the appropriate contracts grants or agreements b In this NPD all mandatory actions i e requirements are denoted by statements containing the term shall The terms may or can denote discretionary privilege or permission should denotes a good practice and is recommended but not required will denotes expected outcome and are is denotes descriptive material 3 AUTHORITY a The Chief Financial Officers Act of 1990 Public Law 101 576 b The National Aeronautics and Space Act Public Law 111 314 as codified in 51 U S C ยง 20113 a et seq 4 ACCPLICABLE DOCUMENTS AND FORMS The National Aeronautics and Space Act as amended 51 U S C ยง 20113 a et seq 5 RESPONSIBILITY a The Agency CFO shall direct manage and provide policy guidance and oversight of Agency financial management personnel activities and operations and ensure that promulgated or proposed Agency financial management policy complies with all applicable Federal laws and regulations and that new or revised financial policy is reviewed by all appropriate Agency personnel prior to promulgation in accordance with NPD 1000 3 This includes affected Mission Directorates and Mission Support Offices if the financial subject impacts work performed by offices external to the CFO community b The Agency Deputy CFO Finance shall provide policy and procedural requirements relating to oversight of financial management personnel and day to day financial management activities and operations and ensure that the policy is reviewed and revised appropriately for continued accuracy and legal sufficiency c The Agency Deputy CFO Budget Strategy and Performance shall ensure that NASA budgets are consistent with Administration policies and guidance Agency strategic plans and Congressional Authorizations and Appropriations and will ensure that policy relating to oversight of budget and performance activities is reviewed and revised appropriately for continued accuracy and legal regulatory sufficiency d NASA managers at all levels shall ensure that the financial operations of their organizations are in full compliance with the official Agency financial management policy and procedural requirements 6 DELEGATION OF AUTHORITY The Agency CFO and Agency Deputy CFOs may delegate the responsibilities listed in paragraphs 5 a and 5 b to a division director within the Office of the CFO 7 MEASUREMENT VERIFICATION Compliance will be measured through existing communications and reporting channels 8 CANCELLATION NPD 9010 2 Financial Management dated October 23 2008 s Charles F Bolden 
